  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Character and Greatness"
      title: "Job\u2019s Character and Greatness"
      number: 1
      content: 'There was a man in the land of Uz whose name was Job. That man was
        blameless and upright and God-fearing and turning away from evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And seven sons and three daughters were born to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then his livestock came to be seven thousand sheep and goats and
        three thousand camels and five hundred pairs of oxen and five hundred female
        donkeys, and he had very many slaves, and that man was greater than all the
        people of the east. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And his sons used to go and hold a feast at each other\u2019s house
        on his day, and they would send, and they would invite their three sisters
        to eat and to drink with them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then when the days of the feast had run their course, Job would send,
        and he would sanctify them. Thus he would arise early in the morning and
        offer burnt offerings according to the number of all of them, because Job
        thought, \u201CPerhaps my children have sinned and cursed God in their heart.\u201D
        This is what Job used to do all the time.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And it happened one day that the sons of God came to present themselves
        before Yahweh, and Satan also came into their midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Yahweh said to Satan, \u201CFrom where have you come?\u201D Then
        Satan answered Yahweh and said, \u201CFrom roaming on the earth and from
        walking about in it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Yahweh said to Satan, \u201CHave you considered my servant Job?
        Indeed, there is no one like him on the earth\u2014a blameless man and upright
        and God-fearing and turning away from evil.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Satan answered Yahweh and said, \u201CDoes Job fear God for
        nothing? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Have you not put a fence around him and his household and around
        all that belongs to him on every side? You have blessed the work of his hands,
        and his livestock has increased in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But, on the other hand, stretch out your hand and touch all that
        belongs to him and see whether he will curse you to your face.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "12: The Adversary\u2019s Attack on Job\u2019s Possessions"
      title: "The Adversary\u2019s Attack on Job\u2019s Possessions"
      number: 12
      content: "So Yahweh said to Satan, \u201CLook, all that belongs to him is in
        your power. Only do not stretch out your hand against him.\u201D So Satan
        went out from Yahweh\u2019s presence.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And then there was one day when his sons and his daughters were eating
        and drinking wine in their firstborn brother\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And a messenger came to Job and said, \u201CThe oxen were plowing,
        and the female donkeys were feeding beside them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the Sabeans attacked, and they took them, and they slew the
        servants by the edge of the sword. But I escaped, even I alone, to tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "While this one was still speaking, another came and said, \u201CThe
        fire of God fell from the heavens, and it blazed up against the sheep and
        goats and against the servants, and it consumed them. But I escaped, even
        I alone, to tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "While this one was still speaking, another came and said, \u201CThe
        Chaldeans formed three divisions, and they made a raid on the camels, and
        they carried them away, and they struck your servants by the edge of the
        sword, but I escaped, even I alone, to tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "At the time this one was speaking, another came and said, \u201CYour
        sons and your daughters were eating and drinking wine in their firstborn
        brother\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And behold, a great wind came from across the desert, and it struck
        the four corners of the house so that it fell upon the young people, and
        they died. But I escaped, even I alone, to tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Job arose and tore his outer garment and shaved his head; then
        he fell upon the ground and he worshiped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then he said, \u201CNaked I came out from my mother\u2019s womb,
        and naked I will return there. Yahweh gives, and Yahweh takes. Let Yahweh\u2019s
        name be blessed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'In all this, Job did not sin and did not charge God with wrongdoing.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Adversary\u2019s Attack on Job\u2019s Person"
      title: "The Adversary\u2019s Attack on Job\u2019s Person"
      number: 1
      content: 'And then one day the sons of God came to present themselves before
        Yahweh, and Satan also came into their midst to present himself before Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So Yahweh asked Satan, \u201CFrom where have you come?\u201D And
        Satan answered Yahweh and said, \u201CFrom roaming on the earth and from
        walking about in it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So Yahweh asked Satan, \u201CHave you considered my servant Job?
        Indeed, there is no one like him on the earth\u2014a blameless man and upright
        and God-fearing and turning away from evil. And still he persists in his
        blamelessness even though you incited me against him to destroy him for nothing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Satan answered him and said, \u201CSkin for skin! All that that
        man has he will give for his life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But stretch out your hand and touch his bones and his flesh, and
        see whether he will curse you to your face.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: "6: Job\u2019s Blameless Behavior"
      title: "Job\u2019s Blameless Behavior"
      number: 6
      content: "So Yahweh said to Satan, \u201CAll right, he is in your power. Only
        spare his life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Satan went out from Yahweh\u2019s presence, and he inflicted Job
        with loathsome skin sores from the sole of his foot up to the crown of his
        head. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So he took for himself a potsherd with which to scrape himself, and
        he sat in the midst of the ashes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then his wife said to him, \u201CAre you still persisting in your
        blamelessness? Curse God and die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So he said to her, \u201CYou speak like one of the foolish women
        speaks. Indeed, should we receive the good from God, but not receive the
        evil?\u201D In all this, Job did not sin with his lips. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Thus Job\u2019s three friends heard of this calamity that had come
        upon him. So each set out from his own place: Eliphaz the Temanite and Bildad
        the Shuhite and Zophar the Naamathite. And they met together to come to console
        him and to comfort him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Thus they lifted up their eyes from afar, but they did not recognize
        him, so they raised their voice, and they wept, and each man tore his outer
        garment and threw dust on their heads toward the sky.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then they sat with him on the ground for seven days and seven nights,
        but no one spoke a word to him because they saw that his suffering was very
        great. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Regrets His Birth'
      title: Job Regrets His Birth
      number: 1
      content: 'Afterward Job opened his mouth and cursed his day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Thus Job spoke up and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CLet the day perish on which I was born, and the night that
        said, \u2018A man-child is conceived.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Let that day become darkness; may God not seek it from above, nor
        may daylight shine on it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Let darkness and deep shadow claim it; let clouds settle on it; let
        them terrify it with the blackness of day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Let darkness seize that night;  let it not rejoice among the days
        of the year; let it not enter among the number of the months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Look, let that night become barren; let a joyful song not enter it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Let those who curse the day curse it, those who are skilled at rousing
        Leviathan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Let the stars of its dawn be dark; let it hope for light but there
        be none, and let it not see the eyelids of dawn '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Job Wishes He Had Died'
      title: Job Wishes He Had Died
      number: 10
      content: "because it did not shut the doors of my mother\u2019s womb, nor did
        it hide trouble from my eyes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CWhy did I not die at birth? Why did I not come forth from the
        womb and expire? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Why did the knees receive me and the breasts, that I could suck? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For now I would lie down, and I would be at peace; I would be asleep;
        then I would be at rest  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'with kings and counselors of the earth, who rebuild  ruins for themselves, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'or with high officials who have gold,  who fill up their houses with
        silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Or why was I not hidden like a miscarriage, like infants who did
        not see the light? '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'There the wicked cease from troubling, and there the weary are at
        rest; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "the prisoners are at ease together; they do not hear the oppressor\u2019s
        voice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Job Wishes He Might Die'
      title: Job Wishes He Might Die
      number: 19
      content: 'The small and the great are there, and the slave is free from his
        masters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CWhy does he give light to one in misery and life to those bitter
        of soul, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'who wait for death, but it does not come,  and search for it more
        than for treasures, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'who rejoice exceedingly,  and they are glad when they find the grave? '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Why does he give light to a man whose way is hidden, and God has
        fenced him in all around? '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For my sighing comes before my bread,  and my groanings gush forth
        like water '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'because the dread that I feel has come upon me, and what I feared
        befalls me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I am not at ease, and I am not at peace, and I do not have rest,
        thus turmoil has come.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Eliphaz\u2019s First Response to Job"
      title: "Eliphaz\u2019s First Response to Job"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CIf someone would test a word with you, would you be offended?
        But who can refrain from speaking? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Look, you have instructed many, and you have strengthened weak hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Your words have raised up the one who stumbles, and you have strengthened
        knees giving way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But now it has come to you, and you are worn out; it touches you,
        and you are horrified. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Is not your fear in God your confidence? Is not your hope even the
        integrity of your ways? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThink now, who has perished who is innocent? Or where are the
        upright destroyed? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Just as I have seen, plowers of mischief and sowers of trouble will
        reap it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'By the breath of God they perish, and by the blast of his anger they
        come to an end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The roar of the lion and the voice of a lion in its prime, and the
        teeth of the young lions are broken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The lion is perishing without prey, and the lion\u2019s whelps are
        scattered. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAnd a word came stealing to me, and my ear received the whisper
        from it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Amid troubling thoughts from night visions, at the falling of deep
        sleep on men, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'dread met me, and trembling, and it made many of my bones shake. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And a spirit glided before my face; the hair of my flesh bristled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'It stood still, but I could not recognize its appearance; a form
        was before my eyes; there was a hush, and I heard a voice: '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Can a human being be more righteous than God, or can a man
        be more pure than his Maker? "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Look, he does not trust in his servants and he charges his angels
        with error. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'How much more dwellers in clay houses, whose foundation is in the
        dust? They are crushed like a moth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Between morning and evening they are destroyed; without anyone regarding
        it they perish forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Is not their tent cord pulled up within them? They die, but not in
        wisdom.\u2019 "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Eliphaz\u2019s Response Continues"
      title: "Eliphaz\u2019s Response Continues"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CCall now, is there anyone answering you? And to which of the
        holy ones will you turn? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For vexation will slay the fool, and jealousy will kill the simple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I have seen a fool taking root, but suddenly I cursed his dwelling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "His children are far from deliverance, and they are crushed in the
        gate, and there is no deliverer\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'whose harvest the hungry eats, and he takes it from behind the thorns;
        and the thirsty pants after their wealth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Indeed, mischief does not come from the dust, and trouble does not
        sprout from the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But a human being is born to trouble, and they soar aloft like sparks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBut I myself will seek God, and to God I would commit my cause. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He is doing great and unsearchable things, marvelous things without
        number\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the one who is giving rain on the surface of the earth and is sending
        water on the surface of the fields, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'to set the lowly on high, and those mourning are lifted to safety. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He is frustrating the devices of the crafty, and their hands do not
        achieve success. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He is capturing the wise in their craftiness, and the schemes of
        the wily are rushed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'In the daytime they meet with darkness, and they grope at noon as
        in the night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he saves from the sword of their mouth, even the poor from the
        hand of the strong. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So there is hope for the powerless, and wickedness shuts its mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CLook, happy is the human being whom God reproves; and you must
        not despise the discipline of Shaddai, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'for he himself wounds, but he binds up; he strikes, but his hands
        heal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'From six troubles he will deliver you, and in seven evil shall not
        touch you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In famine he will redeem you from death, and in war from the power
        of the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'From the scourge of the tongue you shall be hidden, and you shall
        not be afraid of destruction when it comes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'At destruction and famine you shall laugh, and you shall not fear
        the wild animals of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For your covenant will be with the stones of the field, and the wild
        animals of the field will be at peace with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And you shall know that your tent is safe, and you will inspect your
        fold, and you shall not be missing anything. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And you shall know that your offspring are many, and your descendants
        like the vegetation of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'You shall come in maturity to the grave, as the raising up of a stack
        of sheaves in its season. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CLook, we have searched this out\u2014it is true; hear it and
        know it yourself.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Second Speech: A Response to Eliphaz"
      title: "Job\u2019s Second Speech: A Response to Eliphaz"
      number: 1
      content: ' &nbsp;Then Job answered and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CIf only my vexation could be well weighed, and my calamity
        could be lifted up together with it in the balances, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'for then it would be heavier than the sand of the seas; therefore
        my words have been rash, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'for the arrows of Shaddai are in me; my spirit drinks their poison;
        the terrors of God are arrayed against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Does the wild ass bray over grass, or the ox bellow over its fodder? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Can tasteless food be eaten without salt, or is there taste in the
        white of a marshmallow plant? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I refused to touch them; they are like food that will make me ill.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CO that my request may come, and that God may grant my hope, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'that God would decide that he would crush me, that he would let loose
        his hand and kill me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But it will still be my consolation, and I would recoil in unrelenting
        pain, for I have not denied the words of the Holy One. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'What is my strength, that I should wait? And what is my end, that
        I should hold out?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Or is my strength like the strength of stones? Or is my flesh bronze? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Indeed, my help is not in me, and any success is driven from me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CLoyal love should come for the afflicted from his friend, even
        if he forsakes the fear of Shaddai. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'My companions are treacherous like a torrent-bed; like a streambed
        of wadis they flow away, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'which are growing dark because of ice upon them, it will pile up
        snow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'In time they dry up, they disappear; when it is hot, they vanish
        from their place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The paths of their way wind around; they go up into the wasteland,
        and they perish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The caravans of Tema looked; the traveling merchants of Sheba hope
        for them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'They are disappointed, because they trusted; they came here and they
        are confounded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CFor now you have become such;  you see terrors, and you fear. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Is it because I have said, \u2018Give to me,\u2019 or, \u2018Offer
        a bribe for me from your wealth\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "or, \u2018Save me from the foe\u2019s hand,\u2019 or, \u2018Ransom
        me from the tyrants\u2019 hand\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Teach me, and I myself will be silent; and make me understand how
        I have gone astray. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'How painful are upright words!  But what does your reproof reprove? '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Do you intend to reprove my words  and consider the words of a desperate
        man as wind? '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Even over the orphan you would cast the lot, and you would bargain
        over your friend. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CTherefore be prepared, turn to me, and I surely will not lie
        to your face.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Please turn, let no injustice happen; indeed, turn, my righteousness
        is still intact.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Is there injustice on my tongue? Or can my palate not discern calamity?  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Second Speech: A Response to Eliphaz"
      title: "Job\u2019s Second Speech: A Response to Eliphaz"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CDoes not a human being have hard service on earth? And are
        not his days like the days of a laborer? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Like a slave he longs for the shadow, and like a laborer he waits
        for his wages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So I had to inherit months of worthlessness, and nights of misery
        are apportioned to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When I lie down, I say, \u2018When shall I rise?\u2019 But the night
        is long, and I have my fill of tossing until dawn. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'My body is clothed with maggots and clods of dust; my skin hardens,
        then it gives way again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CMy days are swifter than a weaver\u2019s shuttle, and they
        come to an end without hope.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Remember that my life is a breath; my eye will not return to see
        good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The eye of the one seeing me will not see me; your eyes are upon
        me, but I will be gone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'A cloud vanishes, and it goes away, so he who goes down to Sheol
        will not come up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He does not return again to his house, and his place does not recognize
        him again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CEven I will not restrain my mouth; I will speak in my spirit\u2019s
        anguish; I will complain in my inner self\u2019s bitterness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Am I the sea, or a sea monster, that you set a guard over me? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When I say, \u2018My bed will comfort me, and my couch will ease
        my complaint,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'then you terrify me with dreams,  and with visions you terrify me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So my inner self will choose strangling\u2014 death more than my
        existence.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I loathe my life; I would not live forever; depart from me, for my
        days are a breath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CWhat is a human being that you make him great and that you
        fix your mind on him,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'so that you visit him every morning,  you test him every moment?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'How long will you not turn away from me? Or not leave me alone until
        I swallow my spit? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'If I have sinned, what have I done to you, watcher of humanity? Why
        have you made me as a target for yourself, so that I have become a burden
        to myself?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And why do you not pardon my transgression and take away my guilt?
        For now I shall lie in the dust, and you will seek me, but I will be no more.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Bildad\u2019s First Response to Job"
      title: "Bildad\u2019s First Response to Job"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Bildad the Shuhite answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow long will you say these things, and the words of your mouth
        be a mighty wind? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Does God pervert justice, or Shaddai pervert righteousness? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If your children sinned against him, then he sent them into the power
        of their transgression. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'If you yourself would seek God, then you would plead to Shaddai for
        grace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'If you are pure and upright, indeed, now he will rouse himself for
        you, and he will restore your righteous abode. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Though your beginning was small, your end will be very great. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CIndeed, please inquire of former generations, and consider
        what their ancestors have found,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'for we are of yesterday, and we do not know, for our days on earth
        are a shadow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Will they themselves not teach you and tell you  and utter words
        from their heart? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Can papyrus grow tall where there is not a marsh? Will reeds flourish
        without water?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'While it is in its flower and is not plucked, yet it withers before
        all grass. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So are the paths of all who forget God; and the hope of the godless
        will perish, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "whose confidence is cut off and whose trust is a spider\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He will lean himself against his house, but it will not stand; he
        will take hold of it, but it will not endure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He is thriving before the sun, and his plant shoots spread over his
        garden. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'His roots twine over a stone heap; he sees a house of stone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "If he destroys him from his place, then it deceives him, saying,
        \u2018I have never seen you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Look, this is the joy of his way, and from dust others will spring
        up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CLook, God will not reject the blameless, and he will not uphold
        the hand of evildoers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Yet he will fill your mouth with laughter and your lips with a shout
        of joy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Those who hate you will be clothed with shame, and the tent of the
        wicked will be no more.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Third Speech: A Response to Bildad"
      title: "Job\u2019s Third Speech: A Response to Bildad"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job answered and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTruly I know that it is so, but how can a human being be just
        before God? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'If he wants to contend with him, he cannot answer him one time in
        a thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He is wise in heart and mighty in strength; who has resisted him
        and succeeded?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CHe is the one who moves mountains, and they do not know how,
        who overturns them in his anger. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He is the one who shakes the earth from its place, and its pillars
        tremble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He is the one who commands the sun, and it does not rise, and he
        seals up the stars.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He is the one who alone stretches out the heavens and who tramples
        on the waves of the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He is the one who made the Bear and Orion, the Pleiades and the constellations
        of the south. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He is the one who does great things beyond understanding  and marvelous
        things beyond number.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CIf he passes by me, I would not see him;  and if he should
        move on, I would not recognize him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "If he would snatch away, who could turn him? Who could say to him,
        \u2018What are you doing?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'God will not turn back his anger; beneath him the helpers of Rahab
        bow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'How much less can I myself answer him? How can I choose my words
        with him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'whom I cannot answer, even though I am righteous? From my judge I
        must implore grace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "If I summon him, and he should answer me, I do not believe that he
        will listen to my voice\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'who crushes me with a tempest and multiplies my wounds without cause. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He will not allow me to catch my breath; rather, he will fill me
        with bitterness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'If it is a matter of strength, look, he is mighty. But if it is a
        matter of justice, who can summon me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Even though I am righteous, my mouth will condemn me; even though
        I am blameless, yet it would pronounce me guilty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CI am blameless; I do not care about myself;  I loathe my life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "It is all one; therefore I say, \u2018He destroys both the blameless
        and the wicked.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When the whip kills suddenly, he mocks at the despair of the innocent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The earth is given into the hand of the wicked; he covers the face
        of its judge\u2014 if it is not he, then who is it? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CAnd my days are swifter than a runner; they flee away; they
        do not see good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'They go by like papyrus skiffs, like an eagle swoops down on its
        prey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Though I say, \u2018I will forget my complaint; I will change my
        expression, and I will rejoice,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'I become afraid of all my sufferings; I know that you do not consider
        me innocent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'If I shall be declared guilty, why then should I labor in vain? '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'If I wash myself with soap,  and I cleanse my hands with lye, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'then you plunge me into the slime pit, and my clothes abhor me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CFor he is not a mortal like me that I can answer him, that
        we can come to trial together.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'There is no arbiter between us that he might lay his hand on both
        of us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'May he remove his rod from me, and let his dread not terrify me; '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'then I would speak and not fear him,  for in myself I am not fearful.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Continues His Response to Bildad'
      title: Job Continues His Response to Bildad
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CMy inner self loathes my life; I want to give vent to my complaint; 
        I want to speak out of the bitterness of my inner self.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I will say to God, \u2018You should not condemn me; let me know why
        you contend against me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Is it good for you that you oppress, that you despise the labor of
        your hands, and you smile over the schemes of the wicked? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Do you have eyes of flesh?  Or do you see as human beings see?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Are your days as the days of human beings, or your years as the days
        of man, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'that you seek out my iniquity, and you search for my sin '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'because of your knowledge that I am not guilty, and there is no escaping
        from your hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Your hands fashioned me and made me altogether,  then you destroyed
        me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Please remember that you made me like clay, but you turn me into
        dust again? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Did you not pour me out like milk and curdle me like cheese? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You clothed me with skin and flesh, and you knit me together with
        bones and sinews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'You have granted me life and loyal love, and your care has preserved
        my spirit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201C&nbsp;\u2018Yet you hid these things in your heart; I know
        that this was your purpose.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If I had sinned, then you would be watching me, and you would not
        acquit me of my guilt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'If I am guilty, woe to me! But if I am righteous, I dare not lift
        my head; I am filled with shame, and just look at my misery! '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And if my head grows bold, you would hunt me as the lion in its prime;
        and you repeat your exploits against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You renew your witnesses against me, and you increase your vexation
        against me; relief forces are against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So why did you bring me forth from the womb? I should have passed
        away, and no eye should have seen me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I should have been as though I had not been; I should have been brought
        from the womb to the grave. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Are not my days few? Let him leave me alone; let him turn from me,
        and let me rejoice a little. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Before I go\u2014and I will not return\u2014 to the land of darkness
        and deep shadow, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "to the land of darkness, like the darkness of a deep shadow and chaos, 
        so that it shines forth like darkness.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Zophar\u2019s First Response to Job"
      title: "Zophar\u2019s First Response to Job"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Zophar the Naamathite answered and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CShould an abundance of words go unanswered, or a man full of
        talk be vindicated?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Should your loose talk put people to silence? And when you mock,
        shall no one put you to shame?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For you say, \u2018My teaching is pure, and I am clean in your sight.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But, O that God might speak, and that he would open his lips to you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and that he would tell you the secrets of wisdom, for insight has
        many sides.  And know that God on your behalf has forgotten some of your
        guilt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CCan you find out the essence of God, or can you find out the
        ultimate limits of Shaddai? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'It is higher than the heaven; what can you do? It is deeper than
        Sheol; what can you know? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Its measure is longer than the earth and broader than the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CIf he passes through and imprisons someone  and summons the
        assembly, then who can hinder him? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For he knows those who are worthless;  when he sees iniquity, he
        will not consider it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But an empty-headed person will get understanding when a wild donkey\u2019s
        colt is born as a human being. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIf you yourself direct your heart and stretch out your hands
        to him\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "if iniquity is in your hand, put it far away, and you must not let
        wickedness reside in your tents\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'surely then you will lift up your face without blemish, and you will
        be firmly established and will not fear.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For you yourself will forget your misery; you will remember it as
        water that has flowed past. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CAnd your life will be brighter than noon;  its darkness will
        be like the morning. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And you will have confidence because there is hope; and you will
        be well protected\u2014you will sleep in safety.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And you will lie down, and no one will make you afraid;  and many
        will entreat your favor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But the eyes of the wicked will fail; and refuge will be lost to
        them, and their hope is to breathe their last breath.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Fourth Speech"
      title: "Job\u2019s Fourth Speech"
      number: 1
      content: ' &nbsp;Then Job answered and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTruly indeed you are the people, and wisdom will die with you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I also have insight like you;  I am not more inferior than you. 
        And who does not know things like these?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I am a laughingstock to my friends:  \u2018He calls on God, and he
        answers him.\u2019 A righteous, blameless man is a laughingstock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Those at ease have contempt for the thought of disaster,  but it
        is ready for those unstable of foot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The tents of the destroyers are at peace, and there is security for
        those who provoke God, for those whom God brings into his hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBut ask the animals, and they will teach you, and the birds
        of the heaven, and they will tell you; "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'or ask the earth, and it will teach you, and the fishes of the sea
        will declare to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Who among all of these does not know that Yahweh\u2019s hand has
        done this? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In whose hand is the life of all living things and the breath of
        every human being?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Does not the ear test words and the palate taste food for itself? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Wisdom is with the aged, and understanding is in length of days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CWith him are wisdom and powerful deeds, and to him belong counsel
        and understanding. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If he tears down, then it will not be rebuilt; if he shuts a man
        in, then he cannot be freed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Look, if he withholds the water, then they dry up; and if he sends
        them out, then they overwhelm the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CStrength and sound wisdom are with him; the deceived and the
        deceiver are his.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He leads counselors away stripped, and he makes fools of judges. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He loosens the fetters of kings, and he binds a loincloth on their
        loins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He leads priests away stripped, and he overthrows the members of
        ancient families.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He deprives the trustworthy of speech, and he takes away the discretion
        of elders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He pours contempt on noblemen, and he loosens the girdle of the mighty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CHe uncovers mysteries out of darkness, and he brings deep shadow
        to the light. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He makes the nations great, then he destroys them; he expands the
        nations, then he guides them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "He strips away the insight of the heads of the earth\u2019s people,
        and he makes them wander in a pathless wasteland.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'They grope in the dark without light, and he makes them stagger like
        a drunkard. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Fourth Speech Continues"
      title: "Job\u2019s Fourth Speech Continues"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CLook, my eye has seen everything; my ear has heard and has
        understood it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "What you know, I myself also know\u2014 I am not more inferior than
        you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But I would speak to Shaddai, and I desire to argue with God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CBut you whitewash with lies;  all of you are worthless healers.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'O that you would keep completely silent, and that it would become
        wisdom for you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Please hear my argument, and listen attentively to the pleadings
        of my lips. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CWill you speak falsely for God? And will you speak deceitfully
        for him? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Will you show partiality for him?  Or do you want to plead God\u2019s
        case? "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Will it be well, if he examines you?  Or can you deceive him like
        deceiving a human being? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CSurely he will rebuke you  if you show partiality in secret. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Will not his majesty terrify you,  and his dread fall upon you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Your maxims are proverbs of ashes; your defenses are defenses of
        clay. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CLet me have silence, and I myself will speak, and let come
        over me whatever may. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Why should I take my flesh in my teeth and put my life in my hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Look, though he kill me, I will hope in him; however, I will defend
        my ways before him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Moreover, this is salvation to me, that the godless would not come
        before him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CListen carefully to my words, and let my exposition be in your
        ears. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Please look, I have prepared my case; I know that I myself will be
        vindicated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Job Argues His Case with God'
      title: Job Argues His Case with God
      number: 19
      content: 'Who is he who will contend with me? For then I would be silent, and
        I would pass away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201COnly you must not do these two things to me; then I will not
        hide from your face: "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'withdraw your hand from me, and let not your dread terrify me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then call, and I myself will answer; or let me speak, then reply
        to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CHow many are my iniquities and sins? Make known to me my transgression
        and my sin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Why do you hide your face and count me as your enemy? '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Will you terrify a blown leaf? And will you pursue dry stubble? '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CIndeed, you write bitter things against me, and you make me
        reap the iniquities of my childhood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And you put my feet in the block, and you watch all my paths; you
        carve a mark on the soles of my feet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And he himself wastes away like something rotten, like a garment
        that the moth has eaten. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Continues to Argue His Case with God'
      title: Job Continues to Argue His Case with God
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CA human being born of a woman is short of days and full of
        troubles.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Like a flower he comes up, and he withers away; and he flees like
        a shadow, but he does not last. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Even on such a one you fix your eyes, and you bring me into judgment
        with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CWho can bring a clean thing from an unclean thing? No one!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'If his days are determined, the number of his months is with you;
        you have appointed his boundaries, and he cannot cross them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Look away from him, and let him desist until he enjoys his days like
        a laborer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CIndeed, there is hope for a tree: if it is cut down, then it
        will sprout again, and its new shoots will not cease; "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'though its root grows old in the earth, and its stump dies in the
        dust, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'at the scent of water it will bud, and it will put forth branches
        like a young plant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CBut a man dies, and he dwindles away; thus a human being passes
        away, and where is he?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'As water disappears from a lake, and a river withers away and dries
        up,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'so a man lies down, and he does not arise. Until the heavens are
        no more, they will not awaken, and they will not be roused out of their sleep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CO that you would conceal me in Sheol, that you would hide me
        until your wrath is past,  that you would appoint a set time for me and remember
        me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If a man dies, will he live again? All the days of my compulsory
        service I will wait, until the coming of my relief. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You would call, and I myself would answer you; you would long for
        the work of your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For then you would count my steps, but you would not keep watch over
        my sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'My transgression would be sealed in a bag, and you would cover over
        my guilt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CBut a mountain falls; it crumbles away, and a rock moves away
        from its place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Water wears away stones; its torrents wash away the soil of the earth;
        so you destroy the hope of human beings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You overpower him forever, and he passes away; you change his countenance,
        then you send him away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'His children may come to honor, but he does not know it; or they
        may become lowly, but he does not realize it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "He feels only the pain of his own body,  and his inner self mourns
        for him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Eliphaz\u2019s Second Response to Job"
      title: "Eliphaz\u2019s Second Response to Job"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CShould the wise answer with windy knowledge, and should he
        fill his stomach with the east wind? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Should he argue in talk that is not profitable or in words with which
        he cannot do good? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CWhat is worse, you yourself are doing away with fear, and you
        are lessening meditation before God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For your iniquity teaches your mouth, and you choose the tongue of
        the crafty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Your mouth condemns you, and not I; and your lips testify against
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CWere you born the firstborn of the human race? And were you
        brought forth before the hills? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Have you listened in God\u2019s confidential discussion? And do you
        limit wisdom to yourself? "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'What do you know that we do not know? What do you understand that
        is not clear to us? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Both the gray-haired and the old are among us\u2014 those older than
        your father.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAre the consolations of God too small for you, a word spoken
        gently with you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Why does your heart carry you away? And why do your eyes flash, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'that you turn your spirit against God, and you let such words go
        out of your mouth? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CWhat is a human being, that he can be clean, or that one born
        of a woman can be righteous? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Look, he does not trust his holy ones, and the heavens are not clean
        in his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'How much less he who is abominable and corrupt,  a man drinking wickedness
        like water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CI will show you, listen to me; and what I have seen, I will
        tell\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'what wise men have told, and they have not hidden that which is from
        their ancestors, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'to whom alone the land was given, and no stranger passed through
        their midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CAll of the wicked one\u2019s days he is writhing, even through
        the number of years that are laid up for the tyrant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Sounds of terror are in his ears; in prosperity the destroyer will
        come against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He cannot trust that he will return from darkness, and he himself
        is destined for the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CHe is wandering for bread, saying, \u2018Where is it?\u2019
        He knows that a day of darkness is ready at hand.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Anguish and distress terrify him; they overpower him like a king
        ready for the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Because he stretched out his hand against God, and he was arrogant
        to Shaddai; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'he stubbornly runs against him with his thick-bossed shield.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBecause he has covered his face with his fat and has gathered
        fat upon his loins, "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'he will dwell in desolate cities, in houses that they should not
        inhabit, which are destined for rubble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'He will not become rich, and his wealth will not endure, and their
        possessions will not stretch across the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CHe will not escape from darkness; a flame will dry up his new
        shoot, and by the wind of his mouth he shall be removed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Let him not trust in emptiness\u2014he will be deceiving himself\u2014
        for worthlessness will be his recompense. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'It will be paid in full before his time,  and his branch will not
        flourish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CHe will shake off his unripe fruit like the vine, and he will
        cast off his blossom like the olive tree; "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'for the company of the godless is barren, and fire consumes the tents
        of those who accept bribes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "They conceive trouble and bring forth mischief, and their womb prepares
        deceit.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Fifth Speech"
      title: "Job\u2019s Fifth Speech"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job answered and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI have heard many things like these; all of you are miserable
        comforters.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Is there a limit to windy words? What provokes you that you answer? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I myself also could talk as you, if you were in my place;  I could
        join against you with words, and I could shake at you with my head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I could encourage you with my mouth, and the solace of my lips would
        ease the pain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'If I speak, my pain is not relieved; and if I cease, how much will
        leave me? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CSurely now he has worn me out; you have devastated all my company. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Thus you shriveled me up;  it became a witness. And my leanness has
        risen up against me; it testifies to my face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'His wrath has torn, and he has been hostile toward me; he gnashed
        at me with his teeth. My foe sharpens his eyes against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They gaped at me with their mouth; they struck my cheeks with disgrace;
        they have massed themselves together against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'God delivers me to an evil one, and he casts me into the hands of
        the wicked. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI was at ease, then he broke me in two, and he seized me by
        my neck; then he shattered me and set me up as a target for him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'His archers surround me; he slashes open my kidneys, and he does
        not have compassion; he pours out my gall on the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He breached me breach upon breach;  he rushes at me like a warrior. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CI have sewed sackcloth on my skin, and I have inserted my pride
        in the dust. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'My face is red because of weeping, and deep shadows are on my eyelids, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'although violence is not on my hands, and my prayer is pure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CO earth, you should not cover my blood, and let there be no
        place for my cry for help. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So now look, my witness is in the heavens, and he who vouches for
        me is in the heights. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'My friends scorn me; my eye pours out tears to God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and it argues for a mortal with God, and as a human for his friend. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Indeed, after a few years have come, then I will go the way from
        which I will not return. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Fifth Speech, Continued"
      title: "Job\u2019s Fifth Speech, Continued"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CMy spirit is pulled down; my days are extinguished; the graveyard
        is for me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Surely mockery is with me, and my eye rests on their provocation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Please lay down a pledge for me with yourself; who is he who will
        give security for my hand?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Indeed, you have closed their mind from understanding; therefore,
        you will not let them triumph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He denounces friends for reward, so his children\u2019s eyes will
        fail. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAnd he has made me a proverb for the peoples, and I am one
        before whom people spit.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And my eye has grown dim from grief, and the limbs of my body are
        all like a shadow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The upright are appalled at this, and the innocent excites himself
        over the godless. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But the righteous holds on to his way, and he who has clean hands
        increases in strength. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But all of you must return\u2014please come!  But I shall not find
        a wise person among you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CMy days are past; my plans are broken down\u2014 even the desires
        of my heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They make night into day, saying, \u2018Light is near to darkness.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'If I hope for Sheol as my house, if I spread my couch in the darkness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "if I call to the pit, \u2018You are my father,\u2019 to the maggot,
        \u2018You are my mother or my sister,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'where then is my hope? And who will see my hope?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Will they go down to the bars of Sheol? Or shall we descend together
        into the dust?\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Bildad\u2019s Second Speech"
      title: "Bildad\u2019s Second Speech"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Bildad the Shuhite answered and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow long will you hunt for words?  Consider, and afterward
        we shall speak. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Why are we considered as animals? Why are we taken as stupid in your
        eyes? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CYou who are tearing yourself in your anger, will the earth
        be forsaken because of you?  Or will the rock be removed from its place? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Furthermore, the light of the wicked is put out, and the flame of
        his fire will not shine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The light becomes dark in his tent, and his lamp above him is put
        out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CHis strong steps are shortened, and his own schemes throw him
        down, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'for he is thrust into a net by his feet, and he walks into a pitfall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'A trap seizes him by the heel; a snare takes hold of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'His rope is hidden in the ground, and his trap on the path. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CSudden terrors terrify him all around, and they chase him at
        his heels. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'His wealth will become hunger, and disaster is ready for his stumbling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'It consumes parts of his skin; the firstborn of death consumes his
        limbs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He is torn from his tent in which he trusted,  and it brought him
        to the king of terrors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CNothing remains for him in his tent; sulfur is scattered upon
        his dwelling place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'His roots dry up below,  and its branches wither away above.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'His remembrance perishes from the earth, and there is not a name
        for him on the street. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThey thrust him from light into darkness, and they drive him
        out from the world. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'There is no offspring for him nor a descendant among his people,
        and there is not a survivor in his abode. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Those of the west are appalled over his fate,  and those of the east
        are seized with horror.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Surely these are the dwellings of the godless, and this is the dwelling
        place of him who knows not God.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Sixth Speech: A Response to Bildad"
      title: "Job\u2019s Sixth Speech: A Response to Bildad"
      number: 1
      content: ' &nbsp;Then Job answered and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow long will you torment me  and crush me with words? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'These ten times you have disgraced me; you are not ashamed that you
        have attacked me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And what is more, if I have truly erred, my error remains with me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'If indeed you must magnify yourselves against me, and you must let
        my disgrace argue against me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'know then that God has wronged me and has surrounded me with his
        net. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CLook, I cry out, \u2018Violence!\u2019 but I am not answered;
        I cry out, but there is no justice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He has walled up my way so that I cannot pass; and he has set darkness
        upon my paths. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He has taken my glory from me, and he has removed the crown of my
        head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He has broken me down all around, and I am gone. And he has uprooted
        my hope like a tree, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and he has kindled his wrath against me, and he has counted me as
        one of his foes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'His troops have come together and have thrown up their rampart against
        me and have encamped around my tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CHe has removed my kinsfolk from me, and my acquaintances have
        only turned aside from me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'My relatives have failed, and my close friends have forgotten me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sojourners in my house and my slave women count me as a stranger;
        I have become a foreigner in their eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I call to my servant, but he does not answer; I must personally plead
        with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'My breath is repulsive to my wife, and I am loathsome to my own family.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Little boys also despise me; when I rise, then they talk against
        me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'All my intimate friends abhor me, and these whom I have loved have
        turned against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'My bones cling to my skin and to my flesh, and I have escaped by
        the skin of my teeth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CPity me, pity me, you my friends, for God\u2019s hand has touched
        me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Why do you pursue me like God? And are not satisfied with my flesh? '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CO that my words could be written down! O that they could be
        inscribed in a scroll!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'That with a pen of iron and with lead they might be engraved on a
        rock forever! '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But I myself know that my redeemer is alive, and at the last he will
        stand up upon the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And after my skin has been thus destroyed, but from my flesh I will
        see God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'whom I will see for myself,  and whom my eyes will see and not a
        stranger.  My heart faints within me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CIf you say, \u2018How will we persecute him?\u2019 And \u2018The
        root of the trouble is found\u2019 in me,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "be afraid for yourselves because of the sword,  for wrath brings
        punishment by the sword, so that you may know that there is judgment.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Zophar\u2019s Second Speech"
      title: "Zophar\u2019s Second Speech"
      number: 1
      content: ' &nbsp;Then Zophar the Naamathite answered and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTherefore my disquieting thoughts bring me back for the sake
        of my inward excitement.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I hear discipline that insults me, and a spirit beyond my understanding
        answers me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CDid you know this from of old, since the setting of the human
        being on earth, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'that the rejoicing of the wicked is short,  and the joy of the godless
        lasts only a moment?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Even though his stature mounts up to the heaven, and his head reaches
        to the clouds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "he will perish forever like his dung; those who have seen him will
        say, \u2018Where is he?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He will fly away like a dream, and they will not find him, and he
        will be chased away like a vision of the night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The eye that saw him will not see him again,  and his place will
        no longer behold him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'His children will seek favors from the poor, and his hands will return
        his wealth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'His bones were full of his vigor, but it will lie down with him on
        the dust. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThough wickedness tastes sweet in his mouth, and he hides it
        under his tongue, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'though he spares it and does not let it go and holds it back in the
        midst of his palate, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'in his bowels his food is turned, the venom of horned vipers is within
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He swallows riches, but he vomits them up; God drives them out from
        his stomach. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He will suck the poison of horned vipers; the viper\u2019s tongue
        will kill him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He will not enjoy the streams,  the torrents of honey and curds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Returning the products of his toil, he will not swallow;  according
        to the profit of his trade, he will not enjoy,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'for he has oppressed; he has abandoned the poor; he has seized a
        house but did not build it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Because he has not known satisfaction in his stomach, he lets nothing
        escape that he desires.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'There is nothing left after he has eaten;  therefore his prosperity
        will not endure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "In the fullness of his excess he will be in distress;  all of misery\u2019s
        power will come upon him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When his stomach fills up, God will send his burning anger upon him,
        and he will let it rain down upon him as his food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CHe will flee from an iron weapon, but an arrow of bronze will
        pierce him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He draws it forth, and it comes out from his body, and the glittering
        point comes from his gall-bladder; terrors come upon him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Total darkness is hidden for his treasures;  an unfanned fire will
        devour him; the remnant will be consumed in his tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The heavens will reveal his guilt, and the earth will rise up against
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The products of his house will be carried away  like gushing waters
        on the day of his wrath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "This is a wicked human being\u2019s portion from God and the inheritance
        of his decree from God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Seventh Speech: A Response to Zophar"
      title: "Job\u2019s Seventh Speech: A Response to Zophar"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job answered and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CListen carefully to my words, and let this be your consolation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Bear with me, and I myself will speak; then after my speaking you
        can mock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'As for me, is my complaint for human beings? And if so, why cannot
        I be impatient? '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Turn to me and be appalled, and place your hand on your mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when I think of it, I am horrified,  and shuddering seizes my
        flesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CWhy do the wicked live, grow old, even grow mighty in power? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'With them their offspring are established before them,  and their
        descendants before their eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Their houses are safe without fear, and the rod of God is not upon
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'His bull breeds and does not fail; his cow calves and does not miscarry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They send out their little ones like the flock, and their children
        dance around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They sing to the tambourine and lyre, and they rejoice to the sound
        of the long flute. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They spend their days in prosperity, and in peace they go down to
        Sheol. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And they say to God, \u2018Turn away from us, for we do not desire
        to know your ways. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Who is Shaddai that we should serve him, or what would we benefit
        when we plead with him?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Look, their prosperity is not in their hands; the schemes of the
        wicked are repugnant to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CHow often is the lamp of the wicked put out, and their disaster
        comes upon them? He distributes pains in his anger. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'How often are they like straw before the wind, and like chaff that
        the storm carries away? '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u2018God stores up his iniquity for his children\u2019?  Then let
        him repay it to him that he may know. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Let his eyes see his decay, and let him drink from the wrath of Shaddai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'for what does he care for his house after him, when the number of
        his months is cut off? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Can anyone teach knowledge to God, since he himself judges high ones? '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'This one dies in full prosperity,  completely at ease and secure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'His vats are full with milk and the marrow of his bones is moist. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Yet another dies with a bitter inner self  and has not tasted prosperity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'They lie down together in the dust, and maggots cover them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CLook, I know your thoughts and the schemes you devise against
        me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For you say, \u2018Where is the nobleman\u2019s house, and where
        are the tents in which the wicked dwell?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Do you not ask those traveling the roads, and do you not take notice
        of their accounts? '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Indeed, the wicked is spared from the day of disaster; he is delivered
        from the day of wrath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Who denounces his way to his face? And who repays him for what he
        has done? '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'When he is brought to the grave, then someone stands guard over the
        tomb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The clods of the valley are sweet to him; everyone will follow after
        him, and before him they are innumerable.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "So how will you comfort me with emptiness, when fraud is left in
        your answers?\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Eliphaz\u2019s Third Speech"
      title: "Eliphaz\u2019s Third Speech"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CCan a man be of use to God? Yes, can the wise be of use to
        him? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Is it a pleasure to Shaddai if you are righteous, or a gain if you
        make your ways blameless? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Does he reprove you because of your reverence or enter into judgment
        with you? '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Is not your wickedness great, and there is no end to your iniquities? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIndeed, you have required a pledge from your family for nothing,
        and you have stripped off the clothes of the naked. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You have given no water for the weary to drink, and you withheld
        food from the hungry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the land belongs to the man of power,  and the favored lives
        in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You have sent widows away empty-handed, and the arms of orphans were
        crushed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Therefore trapping nets are all around you, and panic suddenly terrifies
        you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'or it is so dark you cannot see, and a flood of water covers you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CIs not God in the height of the heavens? But see how lofty
        are the highest stars.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And you ask, \u2018What does God know? Can he judge through deep
        gloom? "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thick clouds are a covering for him, so that he does not see; and
        he walks about on the dome of heaven.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Will you keep to the way of old that the people of mischief have
        trod, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'who were snatched away before their time,  whose foundation was washed
        away by a current? '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Those who said to God, \u2018Turn away from us,\u2019 and \u2018What
        can Shaddai do to us?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Yet he himself filled up their houses with good things, but the schemes
        of the wicked are repugnant to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The righteous see, and they rejoice, but the innocent one mocks at
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Surely our foe perishes, and fire has consumed their remainder.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CPlease reconcile yourself with him, and be at peace; in this
        way, good will come to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Please receive instruction from his mouth, and place his words in
        your heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'If you return to Shaddai, you will be restored; if you remove wickedness
        from your tent, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and if you put gold ore in the dust, and the gold of Ophir in the
        rock of wadis, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'then Shaddai will be your gold ore and your precious silver.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Indeed, then you will delight yourself in Shaddai, and you will expect
        that God will be good to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'You will pray to him, and he will hear you, and you will pay your
        vows. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And you will decide on a matter, and it will be established for you,
        and light will shine on your ways. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "When they are humiliated, you say, \u2018It is pride,\u2019 for he
        saves the humble.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "He will deliver the guilty, and he will escape because of the cleanness
        of your hands.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Eighth Speech: A Response to Eliphaz"
      title: "Job\u2019s Eighth Speech: A Response to Eliphaz"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job answered and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CEven today my complaint is bitter; my hand is heavy in addition
        to my groaning. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'O that I knew and that I might find him; O that I might come to his
        dwelling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I would lay my case before him,  and I would fill my mouth with arguments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I want to know the words with which he would answer me, and I want
        to understand what he would say to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Would he contend with me in the greatness of his strength? No, but
        he himself would give heed to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'There an upright person could reason with him, and I would be acquitted
        forever by my judge. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CWhen I go forward, he is not there,  or backward, I cannot
        see him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When he works on the left, I cannot perceive him; he turns to the
        right, but I cannot see him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But he knows the way that I take;  he tests me\u2014I shall come
        out like gold. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'My foot has held on to his steps; I have kept his way, and I have
        not turned aside. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'From the commandment of his lips, indeed I have not departed; I have
        treasured the words of his mouth more than my daily food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBut he is alone, and who can dissuade him? And whatever he
        desires, indeed, he does it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For he will carry out what he appoints for me,  and many things like
        these are with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Therefore, I am horrified because of his presence; when I consider,
        I tremble because of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Indeed, God has made my heart faint, and Shaddai has terrified me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Indeed, I have not been silenced because of darkness,  and because
        of me he conceals thick darkness. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Eighth Speech, Continued"
      title: "Job\u2019s Eighth Speech, Continued"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CWhy are not times kept by Shaddai, and why do not those who
        know him see his days? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They remove border stones; they seize flocks, and they pasture them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They drive away the donkey of orphans; they take the widow\u2019s
        ox as a pledge. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They thrust the poor off the road; the needy of the earth hide themselves
        together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CLook, like wild donkeys in the desert they go out to their
        labor as searchers for the prey; the wilderness is their food for the young. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They reap their fodder in the field, and they glean in the vineyard
        of the wicked. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They spend the night naked, without clothing, and they have no garment
        in the cold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They are wet from the rainstorm of the mountains,  and they cling
        to the rock without refuge. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThey snatch the orphan from the breast, and they take a pledge
        against the needy.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They go about naked, without clothing, and hungry, they carry the
        sheaves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Between their terraces they press out oil; they tread the presses,
        but they are thirsty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'From the city people groan, and the throat of the wounded cries for
        help; yet God does not regard it as unseemly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThose are among the ones rebelling against the light; they
        do not recognize his ways, and they do not stay in his paths. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'At dusk the murderer rises; he kills the needy and the poor, and
        in the night he is like a thief. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the eye of the adulterer waits for dusk, saying, \u2018No eye
        will see me,\u2019  and he places a covering on his face. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He digs through houses in the darkness; by day they shut themselves
        in\u2014 they do not know the light "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'because morning likewise is to them deep darkness; indeed, they know
        about the terrors of deep darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CHe himself is swift on the water\u2019s surface; their portion
        is cursed in the land. No one turns toward the path of their vineyards.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Drought and heat snatch away the snow waters, like Sheol snatches
        away those who have sinned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The womb forgets him. The maggot feasts on him until he is no longer
        remembered, and wickedness is broken like a tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He feeds on the barren, who does not have a child, and does no good
        to the widow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Yet he carries off the tyrants by his strength; if he rises up, then
        he cannot be certain of life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He gives security to him, and he is supported, but his eyes are upon
        their ways. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'They are exalted a little while, then they are gone.  And they are
        brought low; they are cut off like all others, and like the heads of grain
        they wither away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CAnd if it is not so, then who can prove me a liar and reduce
        my word to nothing?\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Bildad\u2019s Third Speech"
      title: "Bildad\u2019s Third Speech"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Bildad the Shuhite answered and said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CDomination and dread are with him who makes peace in his high
        heavens. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Is there a number to his troops? And upon whom does his light not
        rise? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CIndeed, how can a human being be righteous before God? And
        how will he who is born of a woman be pure? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Look, even the moon is not bright,  and the stars are not pure in
        his sight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "How much less for a human being who is a maggot, and a human who
        is a worm?\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Ninth Speech: A Response to Bildad"
      title: "Job\u2019s Ninth Speech: A Response to Bildad"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job answered and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow you have helped one who has no power!  How you have assisted
        the arm that has no strength!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'How you have advised one who has no wisdom!  And what sound wisdom
        you have made known in abundance!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'With whose help have you uttered words, and whose breath has come
        forth from you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThe spirits of the dead tremble below the waters and their
        inhabitants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Sheol is naked before him, and there is no covering for Abaddon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He stretches out the north over emptiness; he hangs the earth over
        nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He ties up the water in its clouds, and the cloud is not torn open
        beneath it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He covers the face of the full moon;  he spreads his cloud over it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He has described a circle on the face of the water between light
        and darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CThe pillars of heaven tremble, and they are astounded at his
        rebuke. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'By his power he stilled the sea, and by his understanding he struck
        down Rahab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'By his breath the heavens were made clear;  his hand pierced the
        fleeing snake. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Look, these are the outer fringes of his ways, and how faint is the
        word that we hear of him! But who can understand the thunder of his power?\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Continues His Final Speech'
      title: Job Continues His Final Speech
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job again took up his discourse and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CAs God lives, he has removed my justice, and Shaddai has made
        my inner self bitter. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For as long as my breath is in me, and the spirit of God is in my
        nose, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'my lips surely will not speak falseness, and my tongue surely will
        not utter deceit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Far be it from me that I would say that you are right;  until I pass
        away, I will not put away from me my blamelessness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I hold fast to my righteousness, and I will not let it go; my heart
        will not blame any of my days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CLet my enemy be like the wicked and my opponent like the unrighteous, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'for what is the hope of the godless when he cuts them off, when God
        takes away his life? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Will God hear his cry of distress when distress comes upon him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Or, in Shaddai will he find delight? Will he call upon God at all
        times? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI will teach you about God\u2019s hand; I will not conceal
        that which is with Shaddai. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Look, you all have seen, and why in the world have you become altogether
        vain?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThis is the portion of the wicked human being with God, and
        they receive from Shaddai the inheritance of the ruthless. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If their children multiply, it is for the sword, and his offspring
        do not have enough to eat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Their survivors are buried through the plague, and their widows do
        not weep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'If he heaps up silver like the dust and fashions clothing like the
        clay, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'he makes it ready, and the righteous will wear it, and the innocent
        will divide the silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CHe builds his house like the moth, and like a booth that a
        watchman has made. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He goes to bed with wealth, but he will do so no more;  he opens
        his eyes, and it is gone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Terrors overtake him like the water; a storm wind carries him off
        in the night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The east wind lifts him up, and he is gone, and it sweeps him away
        from his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And it hurls at him, and it has no compassion; he will quickly flee
        from its power. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'It claps its hands over him, and it hisses at him from its place. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Discourse on Wisdom"
      title: "Job\u2019s Discourse on Wisdom"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CIndeed, there is a mine for silver and a place for gold to
        be refined.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Iron is taken from dust, and he pours out copper from ore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He puts an end to darkness, and he searches out the farthest limits
        for the ore in gloom and deep shadow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He breaks open a mine shaft away from where people dwell;  those
        who are forgotten by travelers,  they dangle, they sway far away from human
        beings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'As for the earth, from it comes food,  but underneath it, it is turned
        up as by fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Its stones are the place of sapphire, and the earthen dirt has gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CIt is a path a bird of prey does not know and the black kite\u2019s
        eye has not seen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Proud wild animals have not trodden it; the lion in its prime has
        not prowled over it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He puts his hand on the hard rock; he overturns mountains by the
        roots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He cuts out tunnels in the rocks, and his eye sees every treasure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He dams up rivers from their sources, and he brings secret things
        to the light. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CBut from where will wisdom be found? And where in the world
        is the place of understanding? "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'A human being does not know its proper value, and it is not found
        in the land of the living. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The deep says, \u2018It is not in me,\u2019 and the sea says, \u2018It
        is not with me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CRefined gold cannot be gotten in its place, and silver cannot
        be weighed out as its price. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'It cannot be bought for the gold of Ophir, for precious onyx or sapphire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Gold and glass cannot be compared with it, and its substitution cannot
        be an ornament of refined gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Black corals and crystal will not be mentioned, and wisdom\u2019s
        price is more than red corals. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The topaz of Cush cannot be compared with it; it cannot be bought
        for pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Indeed, from where does wisdom come? And where in the world is the
        place of understanding? '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'It is hidden from the eyes of all living, and it is concealed from
        the birds of the heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Abaddon and Death say, \u2018We heard its rumor with our ears.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CGod understands its way, and he knows its place, "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'for he himself looks to the end of the earth; he sees under all the
        heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When he gave weight to the wind and he apportioned the waters by
        measure, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "when he made a rule for the rain and a way for the thunder\u2019s
        lightning bolt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'then he saw it and talked about it; he established it, and moreover,
        he explored it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And to the human beings he said, \u2018Look, the fear of the Lord
        is wisdom, and to depart from evil is understanding.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Final Defense"
      title: "Job\u2019s Final Defense"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job again took up his discourse and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CO that I were as in the months before, as in the days when
        God watched over me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "when his shining lamp was over my head\u2014 by his light I walked
        through darkness\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "as when I was in the days of my prime, when God\u2019s confiding
        was over my house,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'when Shaddaiwas still with me, my children were all around me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'when my paths were washed in sour milk, and the rock poured out streams
        of oil for me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAt my going out the gate to the city, I secured my seat in
        the square. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Young men saw me and stepped aside, and the aged rose up and stood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Officials refrained from talking, and they laid their hand on their
        mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The voices of nobles were hushed, and their tongue stuck to their
        palate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CWhen the ear heard and commended me, and the eye saw and testified
        in support of me "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'because I saved the needy who cried for help, and I saved the orphan
        for whom there was no helper. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The blessing of the wretched came upon me, and I caused the widow\u2019s
        heart to sing for joy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I put on righteousness, and it clothed me; my justice was like a
        robe and a headband. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CI was eyes to the blind, and I was feet to the lame. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I was a father to the poor, and I investigated the stranger\u2019s
        legal dispute. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And I broke the evil one\u2019s jaw bones, and I made his prey drop
        from his teeth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CAnd I thought, \u2018I will pass away in my nest, and like
        the phoenix I shall multiply my days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'My roots were open to water, and dew spent the night on my branches; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "My glory was new with me, and I was revitalized regularly.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThey listened to me and waited, and they kept silent for my
        counsel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'After my word, they did not speak again, and my word dropped down
        like dew upon them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they waited for me as for the rain, and they opened their mouth
        wide as for the spring rain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'I smiled for them when they had no confidence in anything, and they
        did not extinguish the light of my face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'I chose their way, and I sat as head, and I dwelled like a king among
        the troops, like one who comforts mourners. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Final Defense Continued"
      title: "Job\u2019s Final Defense Continued"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CBut now those younger than I, as far as days, laugh at me,
        whose fathers I rejected for setting with the dogs of my sheep and goats. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Moreover, what use to me is the strength of their hands?  With them,
        vigor is destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Through want and through barren hunger they are gnawing in the dry
        region in the darkness of desolation and waste. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They are picking salt herbs, the leaves of bushes, and the roots
        of broom trees to warm themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They were driven out from fellow people; they shout at them as at
        a thief, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'so that they dwell  in holes of the ground and in the rocks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They bray among the bushes; they are gathered under the nettles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'A senseless crowd, yes, a disreputable brood,  they were cast out
        from the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CBut now I am their mocking song, and I have become a byword
        for them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They abhor me; they keep aloof from me, and they do not withhold
        spit from my face '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'because he has loosened his bowstring and humbled me, and they have
        thrown off restraint in my presence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'On the right hand the brood rises up; they put me to flight,  and
        they build up their siege ramps against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They destroy my path; they promote my destruction; they have no helper. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'As through a wide breach they come; amid a crash they rush on. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Terrors are turned upon me; my honor is pursued as by the wind, and
        my hope of deliverance passed by like a cloud. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAnd now my life is poured out onto me; days of misery have
        taken hold of me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'At night I am in great pain;  my pains do not take a rest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "He seizes my clothing with great power;  he grasps me by my tunic\u2019s
        collar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He has cast me into the dirt, and I have become like dust and ashes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I cry to you for help, but you do not answer me; I stand, and you
        merely look at me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "You have turned cruel to me; you persecute me with your hand\u2019s
        might. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "You lift me up to the wind\u2014you make me ride it, and you toss
        me about in the storm. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Indeed, I know that you will bring me to death and to the house of
        assembly for all the living. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CSurely someone must not send a hand against the needy when,
        in his misfortune, there is a cry of help for them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Have I not wept for the unfortunate,  and grieved myself over the
        poor? '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Indeed, I hoped for good, but evil came, and I waited for light,
        but darkness came. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'My bowels are in turmoil, and they are not still; days of misery
        come to confront me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'I go about in mourning garb, but not in sunlight; I stand up in the
        assembly, and I cry for help. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'I am a companion for the jackals and a companion for ostriches.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'My skin turns black on me, and my bones burn with heat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'So my lyre came to be used for mourning, and my flute for the voice
        of those who weep. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Final Defense Continued"
      title: "Job\u2019s Final Defense Continued"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CI made a covenant with my eyes, so how could I look closely
        upon a virgin? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And what is the portion of God from above or the heritage of Shaddai
        from on high? '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Is not disaster for the evil one and ruin for the workers of mischief? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Does he not see my ways and count all my steps? '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIf I have walked with falseness, and my foot has hastened to
        deceit, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'let him weigh me in the balance of justice, and let God know my blamelessness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'If my steps have turned aside from the way, and my heart has walked
        after my eyes, and my hand has clung to a spot, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'let me sow, and let another eat, and let my crops be rooted out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CIf my heart has been enticed by a woman, and at my neighbor\u2019s
        doorway I have lain in wait, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'let my wife grind for another, and let other men kneel over her, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'for that is a shameful act, and that is a criminal offense.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Indeed, that is a fire that will consume up to Abaddon, and it would
        uproot all my crop. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIf I have rejected my male or female slave\u2019s case when
        their complaint was against me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'then what shall I do when God rises up? And when he enquires, how
        shall I answer him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Did not he who made me in the womb make them? And did not one fashion
        us in the womb? '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CIf I have withheld the desire of the poor from them, or I have
        caused the widow\u2019s eyes to fail, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'or I have eaten my morsel alone,  and the orphan has not eaten from
        it '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "(for from my childhood he grew up with me like a father, and from
        my mother\u2019s womb I guided her), "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'if I have seen the one who perishes because of no clothing or that
        there is no covering for the poor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "if his loins have not blessed me, or by means of my sheep\u2019s
        fleece he has warmed himself, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'if I have raised my hand against an orphan because I saw my supporters
        at the gate, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'then let my shoulder blade fall from my shoulder, and let my arm
        be broken from its socket. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Indeed, the disaster from God was a dread for me, and I was powerless
        because of his majesty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CIf I have made gold my trust, or I have called fine gold my
        security, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'if I have rejoiced because my wealth was great or because my hand
        found a fortune, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'if I looked at the sun when it shone or at the moon moving in splendor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and I was secretly enticed,  and my hand threw them a kiss,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'this also is an iniquity to be judged, for I have deceived God above. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CIf I have rejoiced at the ruin of the one who hated me or have
        exulted when evil overtook him\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'no, I have not allowed my mouth to sin, to ask his life with a curse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Have the people of my tent not said,  \u2018O that someone had not
        been satisfied with his meat\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'An alien has not lodged in the street; I have opened my door to the
        traveler. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Have I concealed my transgressions as other human beings to hide
        my iniquity in my bosom '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'because I dreaded the great multitude, and the contempt of clans
        terrified me, so that I kept quiet, I did not go out of the doorway? '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'O that I had someone hearing me! Here is my signature; let Shaddai
        answer me! As for the written communication that my adversary has written, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'I would surely carry it on my shoulder; I would bind it on me like
        a crown. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'I would give him an account of my steps; I would approach him like
        a noble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'If my land has cried out against me, and its furrows have wept together, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'if I have eaten its yield without payment, or I have caused the breath
        of its owners to die, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "let thorns grow in place of wheat and noxious weeds in place of barley.\u201D
        The words of Job are ended. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elihu Rebukes Job and His Three Friends'
      title: Elihu Rebukes Job and His Three Friends
      number: 1
      content: 'Then these three men ceased from answering Job because he was righteous
        in his own eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Elihu the son of Barakel the Buzite, from the clan of Ram, became
        angry. He became angry at Job because he justified himself rather than God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and he became angry at his three friends because they had not found
        an answer, and they had declared Job guilty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Thus Elihu had waited for Job to speak because they were older than
        he.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When Elihu saw that there was no answer in the mouth of the three
        men, he became angry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Elihu the son of Barakel the Buzite spoke up and said, \u201CI
        am young, but you are old; therefore I feared and became afraid of explaining
        my knowledge to you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I thought, \u2018Let days speak, and let many years teach wisdom.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CTruly, it is a spirit in a human being, and the breath of Shaddai
        teaches them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'It is not the aged who are wise, or it is not the elders who understand
        justice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Therefore I say, \u2018Listen to me; let me also declare my knowledge
        myself.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CLook, I waited for your words; I listened for your insight,
        until you searched out what to say.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I directed my attention to you;  and, look, there is no one for
        Job who refuted, answering his words among you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So do not say, \u2018We have found wisdom; let God refute him, not
        a man.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But he did not direct his words to me, and I will not answer him
        with your words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThey are dismayed; they no longer answer; they have nothing
        to say.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And I have waited because they do not speak, because they stand there
        and no longer answer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I myself will answer my share also; I myself will declare my knowledge
        also, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'for I am full of words;  the spirit within me urges me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CLook, my internal organs are like unopened wine, like new wineskins
        it is ready to burst open. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Let me speak that I may find relief;  let me open my lips, and let
        me answer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Please let me not show partiality to anyone,  and let me not show
        flattery to human beings, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'for I do not know how to flatter,  else my Maker would soon put an
        end to me. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elihu Rebukes Job'
      title: Elihu Rebukes Job
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CBut now, please hear my speeches, Job, and hear all my words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Please look, I open my mouth; my tongue in my mouth speaks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "My words declare my heart\u2019s uprightness, and my lips sincerely
        speak what my lips know.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Spirit of God has made me, and the breath of Shaddai gives life
        to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIf you are able, answer me. Present your argument before me;
        take your stand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Look, before God I am like you;  I myself was also formed from clay. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Look, dread of me should not terrify you, and my hand will not be
        heavy upon you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CSurely you have spoken in my ears, and I have heard the sound
        of your words:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u2018I am clean, without transgression; I am pure, and there is
        no guilt in me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Look, he finds fault against me; he reckons me as his enemy; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "he puts my feet in the block; he watches all my paths.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CLook, in this you are not right\u2014I will answer you: Indeed,
        God is greater than a human being. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Why do you contend against him, that he will not answer all a person\u2019s
        words? "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Indeed, God speaks in one way, even in two, yet someone does not
        perceive it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CIn a dream, a vision of the night, when a deep sleep falls
        on men slumbering on their bed, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'then he opens the ear of men, and he frightens them with a warning  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'to turn human beings aside from their deeds, and he keeps man from
        pride. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He spares his life from the pit and his life from passing over the
        river of death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CAnd he is reproved with pain on his bed, even with the strife
        of his bones continually, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'so that his life loathes bread, and his inner self loathes appetizing
        food.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'His flesh is wasted away from sight, and his bones, which are invisible,
        are bared. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And he draws near to the pit and his life to the killers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CIf there is a messenger beside him, a mediator, one of a thousand, 
        to declare to a human being his uprightness "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "so that he is gracious to him, and he says, \u2018Deliver him from
        descending into the pit; I have found a ransom.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'His flesh is renewed with his youth; he returns to the days of his
        youthful strength. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He prays to God, then he accepts him, and he sees his face with a
        shout of joy, and he repays to the human being his righteousness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CHe will sing to men, and he will say, \u2018I have sinned and
        have perverted what is right, and it was not paid back to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "He redeemed my life from going down into the pit, so I will enjoy
        the light.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Look, God does all these things twice, three times with a person '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'to bring his life back from the pit so that he may enjoy the light
        of life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CListen attentively, Job; listen to me; be silent, and I will
        speak. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'If you have anything to say, answer me;  speak, for I desire to justify
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "If not, you listen to me; be silent, and I will teach you wisdom.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elihu Asserts God\u2019s Justice"
      title: "Elihu Asserts God\u2019s Justice"
      number: 1
      content: 'Thus Elihu spoke up and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHear my words, you wise men, and listen to me, you who know, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'for the ear tests words, and the palate tastes food.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Let us choose justice for ourselves; let us determine among ourselves
        what is good\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "for Job has said, \u2018I am righteous, but God has taken away my
        justice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Should I lie concerning my justice? Though I am without transgression,
        my wound caused by an arrow is incurable.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'What man is like Job, who drinks scorn like water? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he goes on the road in company with instigators of mischief,
        and walks with men of wickedness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Indeed, he says, \u2018A man does not profit when he takes delight
        in God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CTherefore, listen to me, people who have sense:  far be it
        from God that he should commit wickedness  and that Shaddai should do wrong.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Indeed, he will repay according to a human being\u2019s deeds, and
        according to a man\u2019s way he will let it happen to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "What\u2019s more, God truly does not act wickedly, and Shaddai does
        not pervert justice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Who gave him charge over the earth? Or who laid on him the whole
        world? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If he should set his heart to it, and he should gather his spirit
        and his breath to himself, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'all flesh would perish together, and humankind would return to dust. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CBut if you have understanding, hear this; listen to what I
        say.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Shall he who hates justice really govern? Or will you declare the
        Righteous One, the Mighty, guilty?\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "the one who says to a king, \u2018You worthless man,\u2019 to noblemen,
        \u2018You wicked man,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'who shows no partiality to officials  and who does not take note
        of the noble more than of the insignificant,  for all of them are the work
        of his hands? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In a moment they die, and in the middle of the night the people are
        shaken, and they pass away, and they take away the mighty effortlessly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CIndeed, his eyes are upon the ways of man, and he sees all
        his steps. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'There is no darkness, and there is no deep shadow where instigators
        of mischief might hide themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Indeed, he has not yet appointed a time for man to go to God in the
        judgment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He shatters the mighty without investigation, and he sets others
        in their place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Therefore he knows their works, and he overturns them in the night
        so that they are crushed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He strikes them where the wicked stood,  where there are onlookers,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'because they have turned aside from him and have not understood any
        of his ways, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'so that they cause the cry of distress from the helpless to come
        to him, and he hears the cry of distress from the needy, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'but he remains quiet, and who can condemn? And he hides his face,
        and who can behold him? Yet he is over a nation and over a person alike, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'so that godless human beings should not reign, nor those who ensnare
        the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CIndeed, does anyone say to God, \u2018I have endured chastisement;
        I will not act corruptly again; "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "teach me yourself what I cannot see;  if I have done wrong, I will
        not repeat it\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'According to your judgment, must he repay it because you rejected
        this? Indeed, you must choose, and not I, so declare what you know. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Those who have sense say to me, and the wise man hearing me says: '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u2018Job speaks without knowledge, and his words are without insight. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Would that Job were tested up to the end because his answers are
        like those from men of mischief, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "for he adds transgression to his sin; he claps hands among us, and
        he multiplies his words against God.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elihu Condemns Job'
      title: Elihu Condemns Job
      number: 1
      content: 'Moreover, Elihu spoke up and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CDo you think this is justice when you say, \u2018I am right
        before God\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "If you ask what it profits you: \u2018How do I benefit by refraining
        from my sin?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I myself will give answer to you  and to your friends with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CLook at the heavens, and see; and observe the clouds that are
        higher than you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'If you have sinned, what do you accomplish against him? And if your
        transgressions are multiplied, what do you do to him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'If you are righteous, what do you give to him, or what does he receive
        from your hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Your wickedness affects a person like yourself, and your righteousness
        affects humans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CBecause of the multitude of oppressions, they cry out; they
        cry for help because of the arm of the mighty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But no one says, \u2018Where is God my Maker, who gives songs in
        the night, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "who teaches us more than the animals of the earth and makes us wiser
        than the birds of the heavens?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'There they cry out, but he does not answer because of the pride of
        evildoers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CSurely God does not hear an empty plea, and Shaddai does not
        regard it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'How much less when you say that you do not see him, that the case
        is before him, and you are waiting for him! '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But now, because his anger does not punish, and he does not acknowledge
        the transgression at all, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "therefore Job opens his mouth in empty talk\u2014 without knowledge
        he multiplies words.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elihu Extols God\u2019s Greatness"
      title: "Elihu Extols God\u2019s Greatness"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Elihu continued and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CBear with me a little longer, and I will explain,  for I still
        have something to say on God\u2019s behalf.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I will bring my knowledge from far away, and I will ascribe righteousness
        to my maker, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'for truly my words are not falsehood; one who has perfect knowledge
        is with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Look, God is mighty but does not despise anyone; he is mighty and
        good in understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He does not keep the wicked alive but grants justice to the afflicted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He does not withdraw his eyes from the righteous, but he sets them
        forever with kings on the throne, and they are exalted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CAnd if they are tied up with fetters, if they are caught in
        the cords of misery, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'then he declares their work to them, and their transgressions, that
        they are behaving arrogantly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So he opens their ear to the discipline, and he commands that they
        return from mischief. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'If they listen and serve him, they complete their days in prosperity
        and their years in pleasantness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But if they do not listen, they perish by the sword, and they pass
        away without knowledge. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the godless of heart cherish anger; they do not cry for help
        when he binds them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They die in their youth,  and their life ends among the male shrine
        prostitutes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He delivers the afflicted by his misery, and he opens their ears
        by the adversity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And what\u2019s more, he allured you out of distress  into a broad
        place, where in place of it was no constraint; and what was set on your table
        is full of fatness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But you are obsessed with the judgment of the wicked; judgment and
        justice take hold of you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Yes, it is wrath, so that it will not incite you into mockery; and
        do not let the ransom\u2019s greatness turn you aside. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Will your cry for help sustain you without distress, or all the efforts
        of your strength? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You must not long for the night, to cut off people in their place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Take care, you must not turn to mischief, for because of this you
        have been tried by misery. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CLook, God is exalted in his power; who is a teacher like him? "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Who has prescribed his way for him? Or who says, \u2018You have done
        wrong\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Remember that you should extol his work, of which people have sung. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'All human beings have looked on it; everyone watches from afar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CLook, God is exalted, and we do not know him; the number of
        his years is unsearchable. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Indeed, he draws up the drops of water; he distills the rain into
        its mist, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'which the clouds pour down; they shower abundantly on human beings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CMoreover, can anyone understand the spreading of clouds, the
        thundering of his dwelling place? "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Look, he scatters his lightning around him, and he covers the roots
        of the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Indeed, he judges people by them; he gives food in abundance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He covers his hands with lightning, and he commands it the place
        at which to strike. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'His thundering tells about him; the livestock also tell concerning
        what rises.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elihu Extols God\u2019s Majesty"
      title: "Elihu Extols God\u2019s Majesty"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CAbout this also my heart trembles, and it leaps from its place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Listen carefully to his voice\u2019s thunder and the rumbling that
        goes out from his mouth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "He lets it loose under all the heavens, and his lightning to the
        earth\u2019s corners. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'After it, his voice roars; it thunders with his majestic voice, 
        and he does not restrain it when his voice is heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CGod thunders with his voice in marvelous ways; he does great
        things, and we cannot comprehend. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For to the snow he says, \u2018Fall on the earth\u2019; and the shower
        of rain, his heavy shower of rain\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'he stops all human beings from working  so that everyone whom he
        has made may know it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the animal goes into its den, and it remains in its den. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThe storm wind comes from its chamber and cold from the north
        wind. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "By God\u2019s breath, ice is given, and the broad waters are frozen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Also, he loads down thick clouds with moisture; his lightning scatters
        the clouds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they turn around by his guidance to accomplish all that he has
        commanded them on the face of the habitable world.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Whether as correction or for his land, or as loyal love, he lets
        it happen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CHear this, Job; stand still and consider carefully God\u2019s
        wondrous works. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Do you know how God commands them  and how he causes his cloud\u2019s
        lightning to shine? "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Do you know about the hovering of the clouds, the marvelous works
        of the one with perfect knowledge?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You whose garments are hot, when the earth is being still because
        of the south wind, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'with him can you spread out the skies, hard as a molten mirror? '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CTeach us what we should say to him; we cannot draw up our case
        because of the presence of darkness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Should he be told that I want to speak? Or did a man say that he
        would be communicated with? '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So then, they do not look at the light when it is bright in the skies,
        when the wind has passed and has cleansed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "From the north comes gold\u2014 awesome majesty is around God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'As for Shaddai, we cannot attain him; he is exalted in power, and
        he does not oppress justice and abundant righteousness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Therefore people revered him; he does not regard any who think that
        they are wise.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Yahweh Challenges Job'
      title: Yahweh Challenges Job
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Yahweh answered Job from the storm, and he said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CWho is this darkening counsel by words without knowledge? "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Yahweh Interrogates Job'
      title: Yahweh Interrogates Job
      number: 3
      content: 'Prepare yourself for a difficult task like a man,  and I will question
        you, and you shall declare to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CWhere were you at my laying the foundation of the earth? Tell
        me, if you possess understanding. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Who determined its measurement? Yes, you do know. Or who stretched
        the measuring line upon it? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'On what were its bases sunk? Or who laid its cornerstone, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'when the morning stars were singing together and all the sons of
        God shouted for joy? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201COr who shut the sea in with doors at its bursting, when it
        went out of the womb, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'at my making the clouds its garment and thick darkness its swaddling
        band, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and I prescribed my rule for it, and I set bars and doors, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "and I said, \u2018You shall come up to here, but you shall not go
        further, and here it will set a boundary for your proud surging waves\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CHave you ever in your life commanded the morning? Have you
        made the dawn know its place, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "to take hold of the earth\u2019s skirts so that the wicked might
        be shaken off from it? "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'It is changed like clay under a seal, and they appear like a garment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And their light is withheld from the wicked, and their uplifted arm
        is broken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CHave you entered into the sea\u2019s sources? Or have you walked
        around in the recesses of the deep? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Have the gates of death been revealed to you? Or have you seen the
        gates of deep shadow? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Have you considered closely the earth\u2019s vast expanse? Declare
        it, if you know all of it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CWhere then is the way where the light dwells? And where then
        is its place, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'that you may take it to its territory, and that you might discern
        the paths to its home? '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You know, for you were born then, and the number of your days is
        great. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Have you entered into the storehouses of the snow, or have you seen
        the storehouses of the hail, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'which I have reserved for the time of trouble, for the day of battle
        and war? '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Where then is the way where the light is distributed, where he scatters
        the east wind upon the earth? '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CWho has cut open a channel for the torrents and a way for the
        thunder bolts,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'to bring rain on a land where no one lives,  a desert where no humans
        live,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'to satisfy desert and wasteland, and to cause the ground to put forth
        the rising of grass? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Is there a father for the rain, or who fathered the drops of dew? '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'From whose womb did the ice come forth, and who fathered the frost
        of heaven? '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Like stone the waters become hard, and the faces of the deep freeze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CCan you bind the chains of the Pleiades, or can you loosen
        the cords of Orion? "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Can you lead forth the southern constellations at their appointed
        time, or can you lead the Bear with its children? '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Do you know heaven\u2019s statutes, or can you establish their rule
        on the earth? "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Can you lift up your voice to the clouds so that a flood of water
        may cover you? '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Can you send forth lightnings, that they may go? And will they say
        to you, \u2018Here we are\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Who has put wisdom in the ibis,  or who has given understanding to
        the rooster?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Who can number the clouds with wisdom? Or who can tilt heaven\u2019s
        jars, "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'at the flowing of the dust into a cast and the clods cling together? '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CCan you hunt prey for the lion? And can you satisfy the hunger
        of strong lions "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'when they are crouched in the dens, when they lie in the thicket
        in an ambush? '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Who prepares for the crow its prey, when its young ones cry to God
        for help, and they wander around for lack of food?  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CDo you know the time when the goats of the rocks give birth?
        Do you observe the doe deer\u2019s giving birth? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Can you number the months they fulfill, and do you know the time
        of its giving birth? '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When they crouch, they bring forth their young ones; they get rid
        of their labor pains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Their young ones grow strong; they grow up in the open; they go forth
        and do not return to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CWho has sent forth the wild ass free? And who has released
        the wild donkey\u2019s bonds, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'to which I have given the wilderness as its house and the salt flat
        as its dwelling place? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "It scorns the city\u2019s turmoil; it does not hear the driver\u2019s
        shouts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'It explores the mountains as its pasture and searches after every
        kind of green plant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CIs the wild ox willing to serve you, or will he spend the night
        at your feeding trough? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Can you tie the wild ox with its rope to a furrow, or will it harrow
        the valleys after you? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Can you trust it because its strength is great, or will you hand
        your labor over to it? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Can you rely on it that it will return your grain and that it will
        gather it to your threshing floor? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThe wings of the female ostrich flap\u2014 are they the pinions
        of the stork or the falcon? "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Indeed, it leaves its eggs to the earth, and it lets them be warmed
        on the ground, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and it forgets that a foot might crush an egg,  and a wild animal
        might trample it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'It deals cruelly with its young ones, as if they were not its own,
        as if without fear that its labor were in vain, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'because God made it forget wisdom, and he did not give it a share
        in understanding. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When it spreads its wings aloft,  it laughs at the horse and its
        rider. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CDo you give power to the horse? Do you clothe its neck with
        a mane? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Do you make it leap like the locust? The majesty of its snorting
        is terrifying. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They paw in the valley, and it exults with strength; it goes out
        to meet the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'It laughs at danger and is not dismayed, and it does not turn back
        from before the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Upon it the quiver rattles along with the flash of the spear and
        the short sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'With roar and rage it races over the ground,  and it cannot stand
        still at the sound of the horn. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Whenever a horn sounds, it says, \u2018Aha!\u2019 And it smells the
        battle from a distance\u2014 the thunder of the commanders and the war cry. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CDoes the hawk soar by your wisdom? Does it spread its wings
        to the south? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Or does the eagle fly high at your command and construct its nest
        high? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'It lives on the rock and spends the night on the rock point and the
        mountain stronghold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'From there it spies out the prey; its eyes look from far away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And its young ones lick blood greedily, and where the dead carcasses
        are, there they are.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: ' Then Yahweh answered Job and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Job Responds to Yahweh'
      title: Job Responds to Yahweh
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CShall a faultfinder contend with Shaddai? Anyone who argues
        with God must answer it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Job answered Yahweh and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CLook, I am insignificant. What shall I answer you? I lay my
        hand on my mouth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Yahweh Challenges Job Again'
      title: Yahweh Challenges Job Again
      number: 5
      content: "Once I have spoken, and I will not answer; even twice, but I will
        not proceed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Yahweh answered Job from the storm, and he said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Yahweh Interrogates Job Again'
      title: Yahweh Interrogates Job Again
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CPrepare yourself for a difficult task like a man,  and I will
        question you, and you shall declare to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CIndeed, would you annul my justice? Would you condemn me, so
        that you might be righteous? "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Or do you have an arm like God, and can you thunder with a voice
        like his? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Adorn yourself with pride and dignity, and clothe yourself with splendor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Pour out the overflowing of your anger, and look at all the proud,
        and humble them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Look at all the proud, humble them, and tread down the wicked where
        they stand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Hide them in the dust together; bind their faces in the grave. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And I will also praise you, that your own right hand can save you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CLook, Behemoth, which I have made just as I made you; it eats
        grass like the ox. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Look, its strength is in its loins and its power in the muscles of
        its stomach. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'It keeps its tail straight like a cedar; the sinews of its thighs
        are tightly wound. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Its bones are tubes of copper, its limbs like rods of iron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CIt is the first of God\u2019s actions; the one who made him
        furnishes it with his sword.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Yes, the mountains yield produce for it, and all wild animals play
        there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Under the lotus tree it lies, in the hiding place of the reeds and
        in the marsh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The lotus trees cover it with their shade; the wadi\u2019s poplar
        trees surround it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Look, if the river is turbulent, it is not frightened; it is confident
        even though the Jordan rushes against its mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Can anyone take it by its eyes? Can he pierce its nose with a snare? '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "   \u201CCan you draw out Leviathan with a fishhook? Or can you tie
        down its mouth with a cord?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Can you put a rope in its nose? Or can you pierce its jawbone with
        a hook? '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Will it make numerous pleas for mercy to you? Or will it speak gentle
        words to you? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Will it make a covenant with you? Will you take it as a slave forever? '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Will you play with it as with birds and put it on a leash for your
        girls? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Will guildsmen bargain over it? Will they divide it between tradesmen? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Can you fill its kin with harpoons or its head with fish spears? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Lay your hands on it; think about the battle\u2014you will not do
        it again! "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CLook, the hope of capturing it is false. Will one be hurled
        down even at its sight? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Is it not fierce when somebody stirs it? Who then is he who would
        stand before it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Who has come to confront me, that I should repay him? Under all the
        heavens, it belongs to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI will not keep quiet concerning its limbs or concerning the
        extent of its might and the gracefulness of its frame. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Who can strip off its outer covering?  Who can penetrate its double
        harness? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Who can open the doors of its face? Its teeth all around are fearsome. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Its back has scales of shields; it is shut up closely as with a seal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "They are close to one another\u2014  even the air cannot come between
        them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They are joined one to another;  they cling together and cannot be
        separated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CIts snorting flashes forth light, and its eyes are red like
        dawn.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Torches go from its mouth; sparks of fire shoot out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Smoke comes from its nostrils as from a kettle boiling and burning
        bulrushes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Its breath kindles charcoal, and a flame comes from its mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CStrength abides in its neck, and dismay dances before it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Its flesh\u2019s folds of skin cling together; it is cast on it\u2014it
        will not be moved. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Its heart is cast as stone; yes, it is cast as the lower millstone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When it raises itself, the mighty ones are terrified; they retreat
        because of its thrashing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Reaching it with the sword does not avail, nor with the spear, the
        dart, or the javelin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'It regards iron as straw, bronze as rotten wood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'An arrow will not make it flee; sling stones are turned to stubble
        for it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Clubs are regarded as stubble, and it laughs at the short sword\u2019s
        rattle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CIts underparts are shards of a potsherd; it moves over mud
        like a threshing sledge. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'It makes the deep boil like a cooking pot; it makes the sea like
        a pot of ointment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Behind it, it leaves a glistening wake;  one would think that the
        deep has gray hair. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201COn the ground it has no equal\u2014 a creature without fear. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "It observes all the lofty; it is king over all that are proud.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Repentance and Restoration"
      title: "Job\u2019s Repentance and Restoration"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job answered Yahweh and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI know that you can do all things, and any scheme from you
        will not be thwarted. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018Who is this darkening counsel without knowledge?\u2019 Therefore
        I uttered, but I did not understand; things too wonderful for me, but I did
        not know. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u2018Hear and I will speak; I will question you, then inform me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "By the ear\u2019s hearing I heard of you, but now my eye has seen
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Therefore I despise myself and repent in dust and ashes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And then after Yahweh spoke these words to Job, Yahweh said to Eliphaz
        the Temanite, \u201CMy wrath has been kindled against you and against the
        two of your friends, for you have not spoken to me what is right as my servant
        Job has. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So then, take for yourselves seven bulls and seven rams, and go to
        my servant Job and offer a burnt offering for yourselves. And my servant
        Job will pray for you, for I will certainly accept his prayer, so that it
        will not be done with you according to your folly, for you have not spoken
        to me what is right as my servant Job has.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Eliphaz the Temanite and Bildad the Shuhite and Zophar the Naamathite
        went and did just as Yahweh had told them, and Yahweh accepted Job\u2019s
        prayer.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Yahweh returned Job\u2019s fortune when he prayed to him on
        behalf of his friends. Thus Yahweh increased all that Job had twice as much
        as before.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So all his brothers and all his sisters and all those who had known
        him before came to him, and they ate bread with him in his house and showed
        sympathy to him and comforted him for all the disaster that Yahweh had brought
        upon him. Then each one gave to him one piece of money, and each one gave
        to him one ornamental ring of gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So Yahweh blessed Job\u2019s latter days more than his beginning.
        Thus he had fourteen thousand sheep and goats and six thousand camels and
        a thousand pair of oxen and a thousand female donkeys. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he had seven sons and three daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he called the name of the first Jemimah and the name of the second
        Keziah and the name of the third Qeren-Happuk. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And beautiful women were not found in all the land like Job\u2019s
        daughters, and their father gave to them an inheritance in the midst of their
        brothers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Job lived after this one hundred and forty years, and he saw
        his sons and his grandsons for four generations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Job died old and full of days. '
      comments: []
